## 3. Move Zeroes (LeetCode #283)

**Task:** Move all zeroes to the end, keep relative order of non-zero elements.

```java
class Solution {
    public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {
        int slow = 0;
        for (int fast = 0; fast < nums.length; fast++) {
            if (nums[fast] != 0) {
                nums[slow] = nums[fast];
                slow++;
            }
        }
        // fill remainder with zeros
        for (int i = slow; i < nums.length; i++) {
            nums[i] = 0;
        }
    }
}
```

**Common bug:** forgetting the second pass — writing non-zero values forward leaves stale duplicate values in the tail instead of zeros.

**Stretch/alternative (single pass, swap-based):**
```java
public void moveZeroes(int[] nums) {
    int slow = 0;
    for (int fast = 0; fast < nums.length; fast++) {
        if (nums[fast] != 0) {
            int temp = nums[slow];
            nums[slow] = nums[fast];
            nums[fast] = temp;
            slow++;
        }
    }
}
```

---

## ⏱️ Complexity (all three)
- Time: O(n) — single/double linear pass
- Space: O(1) — in-place, no extra data structures

